<TITLE> Nanok slams Ctg WASA for poor ADP execution </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, August 2 (bdnews24.com)The state minister for local government Jahangir Kabir Nanok has reprimanded Chittagong WASA for its poor execution of last year's Annual Development Programme. Among organisations under the local government division, Chittagong WASA marked one of the lowest levels of implementation at 37.72 percent. During an ADP review of the 2008-09 financial year, Nanok said greater scrutiny would now be given to the failing port-city utility provider. Overall ADP implementation under the local government division stood at 93.74 percent for the 2008-09 FY. The development sector was allocated Tk 23,000 crore in the amended ADP for the last fiscal year, of which the local government division received Tk 5,134 crore. Under the local government division, Chittagong and Barisal city corporations both achieved the 100 percent implementation. Rajshahi achieved 99.68 percent, Dhaka 95.39 and the local government engineering department 95.25 percent implementation. b
